<div type="translation" xml:lang="fra" resp="part:sybr part:emfr">
                
<p>
                        
<l>Le roi Lalitāṃkura a fait construire cet édifice nommé Avanibhājana-Pallaveśvara,</l>
                        
<l>Telle une corbeille faite à sa volonté, pour recueillir les joyaux de ses bonnes actions.</l>
                </p>
                
<p>EF: réviser la traduction de svedhā (conservé et non plus émendé en svecchā)? "Telle une corbeille de prospérité (recueillant) les joyaux ..."</p>
        </div>
        
        
<div type="commentary">
                
<p n="1-2">Lalitāṅkura and Avanibhājana are 
<foreign>biruda</foreign>s of the Pallava Mahendravarman I.</p>
                
<p n="2">Avanibhājanapallaveśvara means "
<supplied reason="subaudible">the temple of</supplied> the Lord 
<supplied reason="explanation">that is, Śiva</supplied> of the Pallava Avanibhājana 
<supplied reason="explanation">that is, Mahendravarman I Pallava</supplied>", that is, alternatively "
<supplied reason="subaudible">the temple of</supplied> Śiva 
<supplied reason="subaudible">founded by</supplied> the Pallava Avanibhājana".</p>
        </div>
        
        
